SIMPLE: drover
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drover
<hw>Dro"ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
drives cattle or sheep to market; one who makes it his business to
purchase cattle, and drive them to market.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why, that's spoken like an honest <qex>drover</qex>; so they sell
bullocks.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A boat driven by the tide.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drovy</ent>⟦br⟧
